Distribution: Gauteng, KwaZulu-Natal and Mpumulanga Provinces in South Africa , and Zambia (
Fig. 40
).

Biology: This species shows contrasting habits and has been collected from the soil surface, tree bark and tree canopies. The two specimens photographed live ( Figs 1, 2 ) were actively hunting on bark at night. Both sexes were collected from dense silk retreats constructed in the fissures of bark of mature large trees (
Fig. 3
). There are several attachment lines to the substrate above the retreat as well as slits at the bottom and top ends of the retreat through which the spiders apparently enter and exit.
